---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Headquarters', axa: 'Paris, France', allianz: 'Munich, Germany' },
  { feature: 'Regulation', axa: 'French ACPR (EU)', allianz: 'EU regulated' },
  { feature: 'Network Size', axa: '1.6M+ providers', allianz: '2M+ providers' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', axa: 'Up to Unlimited', allianz: 'Up to €5M' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', axa: true, allianz: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', axa: 'Comfort+', allianz: 'Add-on available' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', axa: 'Excellence tier', allianz: 'Enhanced/Signature' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', axa: '10-12 mo wait', allianz: '12 mo wait' },
  { feature: 'Dental/Vision', axa: 'Comfort+', allianz: 'Add-on available' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Comfort' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Enhanced' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Age 30, ex-US', axa: '€150-200/mo', allianz: '€110-140/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 40, ex-US', axa: '€200-280/mo', allianz: '€135-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 50, ex-US', axa: '€300-400/mo', allianz: '€220-300/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 60, ex-US', axa: '€450-600/mo', allianz: '€350-400/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="AXA Global vs Allianz Care"
  description="Compare AXA Global Healthcare and Allianz Care side by side. Two EU-regulated insurers for expats in Europe and beyond."
  headline="AXA Global vs Allianz Care: European Insurers Compared"
  subheadline="Two European insurance giants competing for expat business. Both EU-regulated, both globally recognized—but with meaningful differences."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    AXA Global Healthcare and Allianz Care are two of Europe's largest insurance providers, both offering international health coverage. For expats in Europe or those who prefer EU-regulated insurers, these are natural choices to compare.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">AXA Global Healthcare</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>French-headquartered (AXA Group)</li>
        <li>Regulated by French ACPR</li>
        <li>1.6M+ providers worldwide</li>
        <li>Essential, Comfort, Excellence, Exclusive tiers</li>
        <li>Strong in Europe and Asia</li>
        <li>Good for French visa applications</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Allianz Care</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>German-headquartered (Allianz SE)</li>
        <li>A+ Superior rating (A.M. Best)</li>
        <li>2M+ providers worldwide</li>
        <li>Base, Enhanced, Signature tiers</li>
        <li>Strong deductible flexibility</li>
        <li>Telemedicine Hub included</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">EU Regulatory Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Both AXA and Allianz operate under EU Solvency II regulations, providing strong consumer protections. For visa applications in EU countries—especially France, Germany, and Spain—having an EU-regulated insurer can simplify the process. Some countries specifically prefer or require locally-regulated coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from AXA Global and Allianz Care."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both providers offer comprehensive international coverage. The main differences are in plan structure, pricing, and specific benefits.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Allianz has a larger provider network (2M vs 1.6M)</li>
    <li>AXA's Exclusive tier offers unlimited coverage; Allianz caps at €5M</li>
    <li>Allianz offers more deductible options (up to €10,000 for 60% savings)</li>
    <li>AXA bundles outpatient/dental/vision in Comfort tier; Allianz uses add-ons</li>
    <li>Allianz includes telemedicine hub in all plans</li>
    <li>Both have similar maternity waiting periods (~12 months)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Plan Structures</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> uses four tiers that progressively include more benefits:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential:</strong> Inpatient and emergency only</li>
    <li><strong>Comfort:</strong> Adds outpatient, basic dental/vision</li>
    <li><strong>Excellence:</strong> Enhanced benefits including mental health parity</li>
    <li><strong>Exclusive:</strong> Unlimited coverage with premium benefits</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> uses three tiers with modular add-ons:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Base:</strong> Core inpatient coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Enhanced:</strong> Higher limits, maternity included</li>
    <li><strong>Signature:</strong> Premium coverage with fertility benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Add-ons:</strong> Outpatient and dental modules available for any tier</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Allianz's modular approach gives more flexibility—you can have comprehensive inpatient coverage (Signature) without paying for outpatient if you don't need it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care is typically 15-25% cheaper than AXA for comparable coverage. Allianz's aggressive deductible options can increase savings further.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Allianz is consistently more affordable at similar coverage levels</li>
    <li>Allianz offers deductibles up to €10,000 (60% premium reduction); AXA caps at €5,000</li>
    <li>Both charge more for worldwide-including-US coverage (~40-50% increase)</li>
    <li>AXA's Exclusive tier is premium-priced but offers unlimited coverage</li>
    <li>Both have payment surcharges for monthly/quarterly (3-5%)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">High-Deductible Savings</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Allianz's €10,000 deductible option can reduce premiums by up to 60%. If you're healthy and want catastrophic coverage (protecting against major illness), this approach makes comprehensive coverage very affordable. AXA's highest deductible (€5,000) offers up to 40% savings.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="Compare actual quotes for your situation."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> claims 2 million+ providers globally, giving them a slight network size advantage. Their provider network is particularly strong in Europe, where they're headquartered.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> has 1.6 million+ providers with particularly strong relationships in France and French-speaking countries. Their European and Asian networks are well-developed.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz:</strong> MyHealth online portal and mobile app. They claim 74% of claims processed within 24 hours. Direct billing at network hospitals. Mixed customer reviews on complex claims.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA:</strong> MyHealth portal and mobile app. Processing typically takes 7-14 days. Direct billing available at network facilities. Claims processing reputation is similar to Allianz—good for routine claims, sometimes slow for complex ones.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer 24/7 multilingual support:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> MediLine medical advice service, telemedicine hub, Expat Assistance Program (counseling, legal referrals)</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Global assistance services, second medical opinion, travel security alerts</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Neither is clearly superior in customer service—both have mixed reviews. Document everything and understand your coverage before you need it.
  </p>

  <h3>Country Restrictions</h3>
  <p>
    Both have some restrictions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Not available if you reside in Germany, Ireland, UAE, Brazil, or sanctioned countries</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Some regional restrictions apply; generally more available than Allianz in certain markets</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose AXA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're moving to France or French-speaking countries</li>
        <li>You need coverage for French visa applications</li>
        <li>You want bundled benefits (Comfort tier)</li>
        <li>You want unlimited coverage option (Exclusive)</li>
        <li>Brand recognition in your destination matters</li>
        <li>You're in a country where Allianz isn't available</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You want lower premiums (15-25% cheaper)</li>
        <li>You prefer modular, customizable coverage</li>
        <li>You want high-deductible options (up to €10,000)</li>
        <li>You value telemedicine access</li>
        <li>You want a larger provider network</li>
        <li>You're comfortable with add-on structure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both AXA Global and Allianz Care are solid choices for expats who want EU-regulated insurance with global coverage. The right choice depends on your priorities.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers better value for most expats. Their pricing is consistently lower, deductible flexibility is greater, and the modular plan structure means you only pay for coverage you need. The 2M+ provider network and included telemedicine are additional advantages.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> makes sense if you specifically need French connections (for visas or provider relationships), want bundled benefits without managing add-ons, or if Allianz isn't available in your country. The Exclusive tier's unlimited coverage is also unique if you want maximum protection.
  </p>
  <p>
    For pure value, Allianz typically wins. For specific situations—especially French expats or those wanting unlimited coverage—AXA may be worth the premium.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
